  'Adding too much graphic elements instead of refining existing ones - refinement is about elevation not expansion. Using text heavily instead of letting design communicate - text must be minimal and serve visual composition. Making reference obvious instead of subtle - should be intuitive only for those familiar. Creating cartoony or amateur work - must maintain sophisticated museum-quality standards. Fonts that don''t serve design - every typographic choice must be design-forward. Elements overlapping or falling off page - professional execution requires perfect spacing and containment. Not emphasizing craftsmanship appearance - work must look like painstakingly crafted by expert, not AI-generated',
  'Design philosophy articulated as 4-6 paragraph aesthetic manifesto. Conceptual reference identified as subtle invisible DNA woven into composition. Canvas created as museum/magazine quality visual art (PDF or PNG). Typography is design-forward and integral to composition. NO overlapping elements, NO margins violations, professional containment. Appearance of countless hours expert craftsmanship. Refinement pass completed focusing on crispness and cohesion. Multi-page works (if applicable) maintain consistent philosophy across pages with unique visual variations. Final output downloadable and portfolio-worthy',
  'Master two-phase canvas design: (1) Create design philosophy/aesthetic movement manifesto (4-6 paragraphs emphasizing visual expression, minimal text, expert craftsmanship), (2) Express philosophy visually as museum-quality art embedding subtle conceptual reference invisibly into composition. Refine to pristine masterpiece level with expert-level detail',
